- Right, so the first thing
to understand about light,

00:10:16.430 --> 00:10:19.923
is that it's just a form of
electromagnetic radiation,

00:10:20.980 --> 00:10:23.620
it's vibrating, it's oscillating, but.

00:10:23.620 --> 00:10:25.580
- When you say it's
vibrating, it's oscillating,

00:10:25.580 --> 00:10:28.500
you mean that photons are actually moving?

00:10:28.500 --> 00:10:30.660
- Well in a sense, photons
they're certainly moving

00:10:30.660 --> 00:10:34.470
through space, we think
about photons as particles

00:10:34.470 --> 00:10:36.070
and that's one way of
thinking about light,

00:10:36.070 --> 00:10:39.230
but we can also think of it
as a wave like a radio wave,

00:10:39.230 --> 00:10:40.890
either way is acceptable.

00:10:40.890 --> 00:10:42.600
And the radio waves have frequencies

00:10:42.600 --> 00:10:45.280
like the frequencies
on the your radio dial,

00:10:45.280 --> 00:10:48.094
and certain frequencies in
the electromagnetic spectrum

00:10:48.094 --> 00:10:51.000
can be detected by neurons in the retina,

00:10:51.000 --> 00:10:52.980
those are the things we see,

00:10:52.980 --> 00:10:55.390
but there's still different
wavelengths within the light

00:10:55.390 --> 00:10:57.800
that can be seen by the eye.

00:10:57.800 --> 00:11:00.540
And those different wavelengths
are unpacked in a sense

