00:58:48.840 --> 00:58:52.810
your visual system is actually
talking to your cerebellum

00:58:52.810 --> 00:58:55.870
saying there's a problem
here, there's an error,

00:58:55.870 --> 00:58:58.820
and your cerebellum is
learning to do better

00:58:58.820 --> 00:59:01.260
by increasing the output
of the vestibular system

00:59:01.260 --> 00:59:03.680
to compensate for whatever that loss was.

00:59:03.680 --> 00:59:05.330
So it's a little error correction system

00:59:05.330 --> 00:59:08.400
that's sort of typical
of a cerebellar function

00:59:08.400 --> 00:59:10.170
and it can happen in many,
many different domains.

00:59:10.170 --> 00:59:13.480
This is just one of the domains
of sensory motor integration

00:59:13.480 --> 00:59:15.283
that takes place there.

