'cause I've done a little bit of diving.

01:00:35.520 --> 01:00:37.750
But what's the story there?

01:00:37.750 --> 01:00:39.860
We don't have to get
into all the differences

01:00:39.860 --> 01:00:41.180
in atmospheric pressure, et cetera,

01:00:41.180 --> 01:00:44.056
but if I'm taking off
and my ears are plugged,

01:00:44.056 --> 01:00:47.340
I've recently ascended, plane
take off, my ears are plugged,

01:00:47.340 --> 01:00:48.580
do I plug my nose and blow out,

01:00:48.580 --> 01:00:49.990
or do I plug my nose and suck in?

01:00:49.990 --> 01:00:52.090
- Right, so the basic idea is that,

01:00:52.090 --> 01:00:57.090
if your ears feel bad because
