01:00:57.230 --> 01:01:01.050
of higher pressure, so if
they pressurize the cabin

01:01:01.050 --> 01:01:02.724
more than the pressure that
you have on the surface

01:01:02.724 --> 01:01:06.040
of the planet, your
eardrums will be bending in

01:01:06.040 --> 01:01:07.060
and they don't like that.

01:01:07.060 --> 01:01:08.690
If you push them more
they'll hurt even more.

01:01:08.690 --> 01:01:11.640
- It's a good description
that the pressure goes up

01:01:11.640 --> 01:01:13.013
then they're going to bend in.

01:01:13.013 --> 01:01:14.700
- Bend in and then reverse would be true

01:01:14.700 --> 01:01:16.680
if you go into an area of low pressure.

01:01:16.680 --> 01:01:20.060
So if you knew you started
to drive up the mountain side

01:01:20.060 --> 01:01:22.170
the pressure's getting
lower and lower outside,

01:01:22.170 --> 01:01:25.514
now the air behind your
eardrum is ballooning out.

01:01:25.514 --> 01:01:26.910
- Yep.
- Right?

01:01:26.910 --> 01:01:27.743
So it's just a question

01:01:27.743 --> 01:01:30.250
